load ../turn-witness.maude

--- The corruption pattern throughout: a receipt claiming "the complete
--- delta is K writes" while the workspace actually moved N > K times --
--- an advancement gate auto-merging work the witness never saw.

--- Hazard demonstrated: the naive finisher claims the mediated write as
--- the whole cut even though a native command also mutated the disk.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-TURN-WITNESS :
  open naiveFin w cmd clean disk(z) seen(z)
  =>* cut(K:Cnt) disk(N:Cnt) RESIDUAL:Cfg
  such that lt(K:Cnt, N:Cnt) .

--- Bite: the sound finisher never under-reports -- once the command
--- taints the turn it declines, and a cut claimed before the command ran
--- is impossible because the finish closes the turn.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-TURN-WITNESS :
  open fin w cmd clean disk(z) seen(z)
  =>* cut(K:Cnt) disk(N:Cnt) RESIDUAL:Cfg
  such that lt(K:Cnt, N:Cnt) .

--- Bite: claiming and declining are mutually exclusive -- one receipt,
--- one honest answer.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-TURN-WITNESS :
  open fin w cmd clean disk(z) seen(z)
  =>* cut(K:Cnt) declined RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Coverage: a clean turn's claimed cut is the complete delta.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-TURN-WITNESS :
  open fin w w clean disk(z) seen(z)
  =>* cut(s(s(z))) disk(s(s(z))) RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Coverage: a tainted turn declines honestly (the receipt says
--- "unwitnessed", not "no changes").
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-TURN-WITNESS :
  open fin w cmd clean disk(z) seen(z)
  =>* declined RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Coverage: a clean turn with NO writes claims the explicitly-empty
--- cut -- distinguishable from declining.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-TURN-WITNESS :
  open fin clean disk(z) seen(z)
  =>* cut(z) RESIDUAL:Cfg .
